<h1>Prediction</h1>

<p class="row">
	<div class="col-md-4"></div>
	<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4">
		<p>Based on your data, our amazing algorithms and a little bit of fairy dust, we have concluded that when buying a <%= @parms[:Brand] %> made of <%= @parms[:Material] %> in the <%= @parms[:Style] %> style and the <%= @parms[:SizeType] %> SizeType, your shoe size would be about <%= @parms[:prediction] %>, with an uncertainty of <%= @parms[:error] %>.</p>
		<p>So you should buy a size <%= @parms[:pref1] %>, or if that's not available, a size <%= @parms[:pref2] %>.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-4"></div>
</p><br>

<p class="row">
	<div class="col-md-4"></div>
	<div class="col-sm-6 col-md-2"><%= button_to "Make another prediction", td_ask_path, class: "btn btn-primary", method: :get %></div>
	<div class="col-sm-6 col-md-2"><%= button_to "Thanks, I'm done now", root_path, class: "btn btn-warning", method: :get %></div>
	<div class="col-md-4"></div>
</p><br><br><br>

<p class="row">
	<div class="col-md-4"></div>
	<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4">Like what we're doing? Think you'll need this again? Save your details to make future visits easier:</div>
	<div class="col-md-4"></div>
</p>
<p class="row">
	<div class="col-md-4"></div>
	<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4"><%= button_to "Save my details", td_solidify_path, class: "btn btn-success", method: :get %></div>
	<div class="col-md-4"></div>
</p>